# GOAT AI — Documentation, commits, recovery

## Documentation update rules

Update docs when behavior changes:

| Change type | File |
|-------------|------|
| Architecture, structure, developer workflow | `README.md` |
| Committed OpenAPI from FastAPI | `docs/openapi.json` |
| LLM-optimized compact API | `docs/api.llm.yaml` (regenerate via `tools/generate_llm_api_yaml.py`) |
| Human-readable endpoints | `docs/API_REFERENCE.md` |
| Env vars, deploy, startup, host ops | `docs/OPERATIONS.md` |
| Current shipped state | `docs/PROJECT_STATUS.md` |
| Phase completion / future work | `docs/ROADMAP.md` |

## Commit hygiene

Before committing:

- No `print()`, commented-out code, or hardcoded secrets/ports/paths
- New functions typed (and one-line docstring where the repo expects it)
- New logic has tests where practical
- `requirements.txt` / `package-lock.json` updated if dependencies changed
- Docs updated per the table above when user-facing or ops behavior changes

## Recovery notes

- If work appears lost, check `git reflog` before assuming it is gone.
- Be careful with `git reset --hard` on the server-hosted checkout.
- Do not commit `.venv/`, PID files, SQLite runtime files, notebook checkpoints, or other machine-local artifacts.
